# Java JSON parser/generator, MIT (c) 2020 miktim@mail.ru

Release notes:
  - Java 1.7+, Android compatible;
  - in accordance with RFC 8259: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/rfc8259/?include_text=1
  - supported Java objects:
      JSON object, String, Number, Boolean, Character, null, Object[] array of listed types;
  - generator converts Character to String;
  - parser implements BigDecimal for numbers;
  - JSON properties are stored in order of appearance/creation.

Overview:
    static Object parse(String json) throws IOException, ParseException;
    static Object parse(Reader reader) throws IOException, ParseException;
    static String stringify(Object object) throws IllegalArgumentException;

  Constructor:
    JSON();

  Methods:
    String toString();
    JSON clone() throws CloneNotSupportedException; // clones only the property list
    List<String> list(); // list properties
    boolean exists(String propertyName);
    Object get(String propertyName);
    JSON set(String propertyName, Object value) throws NullPointerException,  IllegalArgumentException;
    Object remove(String propertyName);

Usage example see in https://github.com/miktim/JSON/blob/master/test/JSONTest.java